> Automatically sends third-party cookies in an HTTP header whenever they are present
in the browser : yes, it does

> Does your web browser implement the blocking of third-party cookies properly?
(firefox), yes

> Does it also disable the usage of the third-party HTML5 localStorage as expected?
No
localStorage stores data with no expiration date, it will not be deleted when the browser is closed
to disable it, set dom.storage.enabled to false in about:config.